### F. Reachability of the external Loki from inside the cluster (air-gapped sanity check)

```bash
# From a grafana collector pod, can it even reach 10.189.35.16:3100?
GP=$(oc -n openshift-logging get po -o name | grep collector-grafana | head -1)
oc -n openshift-logging exec ${GP#pod/} -- \
  curl -sS -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}\n" http://10.189.35.16:3100/ready 2>/dev/null || \
  echo "curl not available in pod — check NetworkPolicy / route to 10.189.35.16"
```

A `429`/`500` here = the external Loki is up but rejecting/erroring. A timeout = network/route problem to the external host.

## Interpreting the results

| What you find | Root cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| S3 endpoint has no `http(s)://` | Internal Loki can't flush | Patch `logging-loki-s3` secret endpoint with scheme |
| Ingester logs show S3 flush errors | Object store unreachable | Fix endpoint/credentials/CA, then restart ingesters |
| `max entry size` errors continue | `maxLineSize` still 1 MB | Raise to 4 MB |
| 429 only on `collector-grafana` pods | External Loki throttling | Raise limits on external Loki at `10.189.35.16` |
| curl to `:3100` times out | Network/route to external Loki | Check NetworkPolicy / firewall to `10.189.35.16` |

## The fixes, once confirmed

```bash
# 1. Fix S3 endpoint scheme (internal console logs + 500s)
oc -n openshift-logging patch secret logging-loki-s3 --type merge \
  -p '{"data":{"endpoint":"'$(echo -n 'https://<your-s3-host>:<port>' | base64 -w0)'"}}'

# 2. Raise maxLineSize + perStreamRateLimit (apply edited lokistack.yaml)
#    maxLineSize: 4194304 ; perStreamRateLimit: 20 ; perStreamRateLimitBurst: 60

# 3. External Grafana 429 — raise ingestion_rate_mb / per_stream_rate_limit
#    in the external Loki's OWN runtime config at 10.189.35.16 (not operator-managed)
```

The single most important command in all of this is the **S3 endpoint decode** (section A) — if that comes back without a scheme, you've found why the internal console is missing logs and producing 500s. Run that first and share what it returns (redact the host) and I'll tell you the exact patch.
